Chery Tiggo8, a vehicle assembled by PAN Nigeria, has won the ‘Quality Product Award’ at the recent 43rd Kaduna International Trade Fair in Kaduna. A statement from the company said the award was presented by Dr Haliru Musa Soba, the Permanent Secretary of the Ministry of Business, Innovation and Technology, Kaduna State at the closing ceremony of the fair. The Managing Director, PAN Nigeria, Ms Taiwo Oluleye congratulated members of the Kaduna Chambers of Commerce, Industry, Mines & Agriculture (KADCCIMA) for their consistency and tenacity in organizing the annual fair. On the award, Oluleye said: “In the last 50 Years, PAN has continued to produce durable and quality vehicles with our customers in mind and the award-winning Tiggo8 is an attestation to our commitment to excellence.” Earlier, the Minister of Industry, Trade and Investment, Otunba Adeniyi Adebayo had commended PAN Nigeria for the introduction of Tiggo8, for its distinct features and robust style, anticipating the model will serve the needs of the targeted segment. As PAN’s flagship, the Chery Tiggo8 is a seven-seat SUV produced at PAN’s Kaduna plant.  The Tiggo 8 is packed with luxury and safety features adopting the most modern technology. Chery motors have gradually conquered demanding consumers across international markets with its outstanding technologies and reliable quality.  These are the unique values PAN hopes to extend to Nigeria’s automobile consumers. 